---
import Card from "./Card.astro";
---

<div class="slots-demo">
  <p class="intro">
    Astro components accept <strong>slots</strong> — named injection points for arbitrary HTML/components.
    Unlike React children, slots are resolved at build time with zero JS overhead.
  </p>

  <div class="grid">
    <div class="example">
      <div class="example-label">All slots filled</div>
      <Card accent="#4a4">
        <span slot="header">Custom Header via slot="header"</span>
        <p>Default slot body content. <strong>Can be any HTML.</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>item one</li>
          <li>item two</li>
        </ul>
        <span slot="footer">Custom footer via slot="footer"</span>
      </Card>
      <pre class="usage"><code>{`<Card>
  <span slot="header">Custom Header</span>
  <p>Default slot content</p>
  <span slot="footer">Custom footer</span>
</Card>`}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="example">
      <div class="example-label">Only default slot — named slots fall back</div>
      <Card accent="#a84" title="Fallback Header (from prop)">
        <p>Only the default slot is filled. The footer slot shows its fallback content defined inside Card.astro.</p>
      </Card>
      <pre class="usage"><code>{`<Card title="Fallback Header">
  <p>Only default slot filled</p>
  <!-- footer → uses fallback -->
</Card>`}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="example">
      <div class="example-label">Only named slots — default slot falls back</div>
      <Card accent="#48a">
        <span slot="header">Named header only</span>
        <!-- default slot intentionally empty → fallback renders -->
        <span slot="footer">Named footer only</span>
      </Card>
      <pre class="usage"><code>{`<Card>
  <span slot="header">Header</span>
  <!-- no body → "No default slot content" fallback -->
  <span slot="footer">Footer</span>
</Card>`}</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="api-box">
    <strong>Slot API in Card.astro</strong>
    <pre><code>{`// Check if a named slot was provided
Astro.slots.has("header")   // → boolean
Astro.slots.has("footer")   // → boolean

// Render slots
<slot />                    // default slot
<slot name="header" />      // named slot
<slot name="footer">        // named slot with fallback
  <span>Default footer</span>
</slot>`}</code></pre>
  </div>

  <div class="note">
    Slots are a zero-cost composition primitive — no React context, no JS, no runtime overhead.
    Entire subtrees render at build time inside the parent template.
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .slots-demo { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; }
  .intro { color: #555; font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 24px; }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .example { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }

  .example-label {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: bold;
    color: #555;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }

  .usage {
    background: #1e1e2e;
    color: #cdd6f4;
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 10px 12px;
    margin: 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }
  .usage code { font-family: "Fira Code", monospace; font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.6; }

  .api-box {
    background: #1e1e2e;
    color: #cdd6f4;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    font-size: 13px;
  }
  .api-box strong {
    display: block;
    color: #89b4fa;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    font-size: 12px;
  }
  .api-box pre { margin: 0; overflow-x: auto; }
  .api-box code { font-family: "Fira Code", monospace; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6; }

  .note {
    background: #f0f4ff;
    border: 1px solid #c0ccff;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
</style>
